Jubei,<br>
<br>
You're partly right. <br>
<br>
The thing that sets off peoples' gag reflex is that some of these guys are actually the nicest you ever wanna meet, like the guy who rezzed me no questions asked even though I flamed his guild a while back (or perhaps *because* I flamed his guild.) Or Cattie who handles guild flames with a patience and tact that would make a UN diplomat envious. Or Arnwolf who I grouped with a long time ago and he was really cool. Hell, even Elwyn who didn't treat me like a gimp (oh jeez, I'm picking up Da'kor vocabulary, someone shoot me) when I bugged him with gimp-like questions as a lowbie.<br>
<br>
On the other hand there are a couple handfuls of people in this guild who would definitely qualify as industrial-grade pricks. People like Kzzern for whom anybody that isn't up to his holiness's exacting standards is a gimp, a tool, a no-talent-loser or all-of-the-above.<br>
<br>
And basically that's why when you happen to see a &quot;Da`kor&quot; tag over someone's head, it gets you wondering if you're about to catch a rez or a train (or both, with a talk-down about how you &quot;shouldn't have been sitting there, didn't you know that you gimp?&quot;)<br>
<br>
This is gonna sound like a flame but honestly I don't intend it as such :<br>
<br>
The whole nice-guy/asshole mix is not a result of one particular guild, but rather as a result of the whole &quot;uberguild&quot; scene. The high level game is challenging, and you need people with certain skill sets, whether they're an asshole or not, as long as they're not an asshole in-guild.<br>
<br>
When your guild needs clerics, they need clerics. As long as they show a measure of respect to their own guildies, they can essentially be assholes to everyone else.<br>
<br>
And if you really have a burning desire to know, I've met a couple of assholes from MS too, not many, just two. But like what am I gonna do about it? Post on your board about them? I'd prolly get laughed off fast so the guild doesn't lose face, maybe be labeled &quot;gimptastic&quot; while they chide the offender to &quot;please try to avoid screwing over the peasants, they come here and raise a ruckus and then we have to shoo them off.&quot;<br>
<br>
And that's not the fault of the guilds. It's the fault of the game for requiring that people spend obscene amounts of time getting ahead or risk becoming second-class Norrathian citizens.<br>
<br>
Salian<br>
